50.  In relation to each type of scheme, the Registrar shall have the
power to specify—
(a)  the duties, obligations and conduct of a management
company;
(b)  the duties and obligations of the trustees;
(c)  the calculation of issued price and buy back price of each
unit of interest;
(d)  the management of funds of the scheme;
(e)  the requirements relating to meetings of interest holders;
and
(f)  any other matters to the benefit of interest holders.
